   <titleInfo>
      <title>Life magazine photo, 415CAL Manbetu male showing extreme fronto-occipital deformatio</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>Manbetu male, showing extreme fronto-occipital deformation, produced by tightly binding the head with fiber bands while the infant's skull bones are still soft. The skull must grow in some direction, so it grows upward, causing the skull to elongate and narrowing the eyes so they can hardly be opened.</abstract>
